3_s
With the Confederacy having provided military assistance to France in its invasion of Mexico, the French are now willing to strike an export deal of their weapons for the use of the Confederacy. The French Minie Rifle is a good all-around service rifle, while Canon Obusier de 12 is the gun-howitzer, known as the 12-pounder "Napoleon" in America. This import deal will come in handy, especially if the Confederate weapons industry continues to struggle to produce the needed number of guns.
Minie Rifles and 12-pounder gun-howitzers import deals.


