5_s
"Hall's Carbines" are considered obsolete surplus weapons of no use. A private arms dealer has negotiated a deal with the head of the U.S. Ordnance Bureau to purchase these weapons with a very cheap price, and to sell them to another dealer, who would modernize them after loaning the required money from private investors and bankers, and then sell them with a much higher price back to the Government for military use, making a few inverstors and arms dealers rather rich in the process.\nNothing suspicious about that.
Hall Rifles and Hall Carbines bought to equip 1 brigade each.
01-09-1861

