Finance Confederate weapons production, providing captured machinery, to produce domestic versions of the U.S. service rifles, mainly copies of the Springfield model 1855. The produced weapons, Fayetteville Rifle-Muskets and Richmond Rifles, are of sufficient quality to arm the Confederate infantry, and the shorter Richmond Carbine is also suited for mounted troops.
Fayetteville Rifle-Muskets, Richmond Rifles and Carbines in production.

01-01-1862
