Finance the weapon industry to mass produce simple cast artillery weapons, that do not require sophisticated metallurgy and machinery. Cast bronze weapons that can be produced are the M1857 12-pounder "Napoleon," based on the French modele 1853 Canon Obusier de 12, or "Canon de l'Empereur," and the James Rifle, which can also be produced by adding rifling to old M1841 6-pounder brass guns.
12-pounder Napoleon Guns and 14-pounder James Rifles in production.
01-08-1861
