Finance the weapons industry to allow production of more advanced rifled artillery. These weapon types, 3-inch Ordnance Rifle and 6-pounder Wiard Rifle, are made from wrought iron, which requires more advanced machinery, resulting in more durable and accurate guns when compared to cast artillery. To mass produce these weapons, a good level of national industrialization is required.
3-inch Ordnance Rifles and 6-pounder Wiard Rifles in production.
01-01-1862

