Finance the weapon industry to allow production of modern Parrott Rifles. The Parrott Rifle was invented by Captain Robert P. Parrott. First of these weapons was created in 1860 and the weapon type was patented in 1861. The Parrott is manufactured with a combination of cast and wrought iron, making it accurate, but a bit unreliable. The field armies can utilize 10-, 20- and 30-pounder versions of the gun.
10-, 20- and 30-pounder Parrott Rifles in production.
