Finance a one-time purchase of novel rapid-fire weapons.\nThe Gatling gun is designed by Dr. Richard J. Gatling. The gun is operated by a hand-crank mechanism, with six barrels revolving around a central shaft. Each barrel fires once per revolution at about the same position. This allows an unusually high rate-of-fire.\nThe Coffee Mill Gun, or Agar gun, after the inventor Wilson Agar, too, uses a hand crank, feeding rounds into the weapon from a hopper, and firing them one by one.\nWhile both weapons fire like "an army in six feet square", the weapons are condemned by the Ordnance Department for using too much ammunition to be practical on the battlefield. For that reason, the weapons will not be financed into mass production.
Gatling and Coffee Mill Guns bought to equip 8 batteries of 4 guns each.


