Finance the Confederate weapon industry to produce southern artillery.\nThe 1-pounder Williams Gun is designed by Captain D.R. Williams, of Covington, Kentucky. It's a breech-loading, rapid-fire cannon that is operated by a hand-crank, firing up to 40 rounds a minute.\nThe 12-pounder Napoleon smoothbore is much liked by the southern gunners. Due to brass shortage, cast iron can be used to produce a cheaper, but less durable and reliable, version of the weapon.\nAs the 1-pdr Williams Gun is of peculiar design, only a one-time purchase of less than 50 pieces is made, and the weapon will not enter mass production.
12-pounder Iron Napoleons in production. 1-pounder Williams Guns bought to equip 12 batteries of 4 guns.

