In America in 1860, there's no lack of weapons. But many of the weapons are already old and obsolete, including a hodgepodge of smoothbore muskets, aging hunting weapons, and the like. A quick option to acquire a number of rifles to arm the volunteers is to modify the existing smoothbores into rifled muskets. The modified, rebored muskets are cheap to produce, but of questionable quality. But they are still better than nothing.
Rebored Muskets in production.
