Finance mass production of rapid-firing, medium range carbines, that can be used to arm infantry and cavalry units alike. While the range cannot match that of modern rifle-muskets, the rate of fire is higher, allowing inflicting heavy casualties in a short period of time, while in close combat. The rate of fire also means that units will burn through their ammunition more rapidly, which can could result in logistical problems on the field.
Joslyn Rifled Carbines, Maynard, Merrill Carbines in production.


