Finance mass production of breech-loading Sharps Rifles and Carbines. Designed by Christian Sharps in 1848, these very accurate weapons saw use during the Bleeding Kansas crisis of 1855-1859. The Sharps Carbine, in particular, is preferred by many cavalry troopers, and it has the potential of becoming the standard cavalry carbine for the U.S. Army. But arming infantry units with such rapid-firing weapons has been rejected as impractical due to ammo consumption and hence logistical challenges.
Sharps Rifles and Carbines in production.
