Finance mass production of Springfield Armory's modified and cheaper to produce Springfield Rifle-Muskets.\nBefore the war, some 75,000 Springfield rifles of Model 1855 were produced for the regular army. When the secession crisis started, many armories were left in Confederate hands.\nThe urgent need for large numbers of weapons saw Springfield Armory simplify the Model 1855 by the removal of the Maynard tape primer and a few other minor alterations.
Springfield Rifle-Muskets in production.
