Finance warship designers and shipyards to allow construction of ironclad warship types, upgraded from traditional wooden sloops and frigates. With heavy armor plating, the Broadside Ironclads and Ironclad Frigates can withstand enemy fire much better than traditional wooden warships. Being more traditional in design, the ships have gun decks and no turrets, which requires more maneuvering during naval engagements.\nConstruction of these ship types requires advanced (level 3) shipyards.
Broadside Ironclads and Ironclad Frigates available.
01-01-1862

