Finance economic reforms that will directly influence the nation's credit rating. A credit rating is an evaluation of the credit risk of a prospective debtor, predicting their ability to pay back the debt, and an implicit forecast of the likelihood of the debtor defaulting. When the credit rating is high, cheaper loans are offered and the interest rate remains manageable.\nEach level of this project will further increase the national credit rating with one step.
National credit rating


