Normally in an artillery battery, the gunners are moving on foot. This reduces their mobility to that of infantry. To be able to support the fast-moving cavalry, an artillery battery needs better mobility. This is achieved by adding sufficient number of horses for all the gunners to be able to ride. Only lighter artillery pieces are available for the horse-artillery batteries.\nThis project allows recruitment of horse-artillery unit type.
Horse-Artillery available.
